  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Photograph</ab>
      <ab type="lido:event" subtype="creation">
        <date>1939</date>
      <persName role="Photographer"><forename>Alija M.</forename><surname>Akšamija</surname><ref type="context" target="info:fedora/context:siba.pn.be7b6d09">Akšamija, Alija M.</ref></persName></ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Upper body shot of an older Orthodox man in <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=B4">Baščaršija</ref>. He is wearing a black cap made from dark lambskin, a tattered white shirt and over it a <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=D9">džamadan</ref> and <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=J1">jelek</ref> modestly adorned with gajtans. He poses in the lower left corner of the frame, smiling gently into the camera, and holding a bag unter his arm with a white cylindrical object and a sachet in his hands in front of him, as if to roll himself a cigarette. Behind him is a view of a bazaar street and the <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=B5">Baščaršija Mosque</ref>.</ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet" subtype="comment">The man is a peasant from the surroundings of Sarajevo. Analogue photographic process, negative-positive (Agfa Isopan 17 DIN). Original preserved as a positive on silver bromine paper, stored as a print and a digital record.</ab>
